WEBVTT

00:01.201 --> 00:05.304
Previously on "The Making
of the Mob: Chicago."

00:05.406 --> 00:08.240
After the death
of their mentor, Al Capone,

00:08.342 --> 00:10.109
Tony Accardo and Paul Ricca

00:10.211 --> 00:12.811
assume control
of the Chicago Outfit

00:12.913 --> 00:15.414
and thanks to their expansion
into Las Vegas,

00:15.516 --> 00:18.684
their empire is bigger
and more profitable than ever.

00:21.389 --> 00:23.722
But now they face a new threat.

00:23.824 --> 00:26.458
Ambitious young attorney,
Robert F. Kennedy,

00:26.560 --> 00:29.661
who targets the Outfit's
most visible member,

00:29.764 --> 00:31.764
acting boss, Sam Giancana.

00:31.866 --> 00:35.434
Would you tell us anything about
any of your operations,

00:35.536 --> 00:38.103
or are you just going to giggle
every time I ask you a question?

00:38.205 --> 00:40.105
I decline to answer
because I honestly believe

00:40.207 --> 00:41.940
my answer might tend
to incriminate me.

00:42.043 --> 00:45.244
But Giancana only makes
the situation worse.

00:45.346 --> 00:46.412
Have you lost your mind?!

00:46.514 --> 00:47.513
Well, what am
I supposed to do?

00:47.615 --> 00:49.481
You fix it.

00:49.583 --> 00:51.417
With the relationship
between the two

00:51.519 --> 00:53.919
Mafia kingpins
falling apart

00:54.021 --> 00:56.021
and pressure from the federal
government mounting,

00:56.123 --> 00:59.858
the final chapter of the Outfit
is about to begin,

00:59.960 --> 01:02.294
and the fate of Al Capone's
criminal empire

01:02.396 --> 01:04.328
hangs in the balance.

01:04.432 --> 01:07.766
I want to hit them
where it hurts most.

01:07.868 --> 01:09.535
Get your hands off of me!

01:11.739 --> 01:16.507
-SubRip & non-HI by Rapunzel-

01:55.182 --> 01:58.016
Head of the Chicago Mob,
Tony Accardo

01:58.119 --> 02:00.219
sits at the top of
the country's most powerful

02:00.321 --> 02:04.723
criminal syndicate,
the Outfit.

02:04.825 --> 02:08.227
But now, he's facing
his biggest challenge yet

02:08.329 --> 02:11.997
after his second in command,
acting boss Sam Giancana

02:12.099 --> 02:15.167
becomes a target
of the federal government,

02:15.269 --> 02:18.370
drawing more unwanted attention
to the organization.

02:20.474 --> 02:24.042
There's a degree of flamboyance
to Sam Giancana, which in a way

02:24.145 --> 02:27.779
is bad for the Outfit
and bad for organized crime

02:27.882 --> 02:30.782
because they really like to fly
under the radar.

02:30.885 --> 02:33.585
And Tony Accardo
got upset with him.

02:37.024 --> 02:40.826
♪♪

02:44.865 --> 02:47.266
But just as tensions between
the two mob kingpins

02:47.368 --> 02:49.935
reach a breaking point,

02:50.037 --> 02:52.905
one phone call changes
everything.

03:09.256 --> 03:10.656
This is Sam.

03:13.260 --> 03:15.160
Joe Kennedy?

03:15.262 --> 03:16.495
What does he want?

03:19.667 --> 03:21.133
A sit down.

03:22.603 --> 03:24.603
What do you
think he's after?

03:24.705 --> 03:28.407
I don't know.

03:28.509 --> 03:31.243
But if he wants to talk,

03:31.345 --> 03:33.045
I think we should hear
what he has to say.

03:37.084 --> 03:39.585
All right.

03:39.687 --> 03:41.386
Set the meeting.

03:46.794 --> 03:50.495
♪♪

03:52.800 --> 03:55.601
Joseph P. Kennedy
is a self-made businessman

03:55.703 --> 04:00.105
whose net worth is valued at an
estimated $300 million dollars,

04:00.207 --> 04:05.444
placing him among the top
20 richest people in America.

04:05.546 --> 04:10.148
Now, he's using his power
to build a political dynasty,

04:10.284 --> 04:12.551
and he'll stop at nothing
to make it happen.

04:28.068 --> 04:30.168
Well?

04:30.271 --> 04:31.670
What can we
do for you?

04:33.741 --> 04:38.176
Well, this is
a little unusual.

04:38.279 --> 04:41.813
The upcoming election...

04:41.915 --> 04:45.851
My son is running
for office.

04:45.953 --> 04:47.085
I'm sure you've
read about him.

04:47.187 --> 04:51.023
He's on all
the magazine covers.

04:51.125 --> 04:54.226
John.

04:54.328 --> 04:56.061
John was born
to be president.

05:00.367 --> 05:04.202
So, what are we
talking about here?

05:04.305 --> 05:07.372
What if I could use a little
help from your organization?

05:08.375 --> 05:10.142
Okay...

05:11.478 --> 05:13.445
We're listening.

05:13.547 --> 05:15.947
I understand that

05:16.050 --> 05:20.952
you have a lot of pull with
the union vote in Illinois.

05:21.055 --> 05:25.290
Those electoral votes
could get him across the line.

05:25.392 --> 05:26.625
That could be
the little push

05:26.727 --> 05:31.263
that could make
all the difference

05:31.365 --> 05:33.098
And why would we do that?

05:33.200 --> 05:36.635
No offense, but your other
son's an asshole.

05:36.737 --> 05:38.136
Hey.

05:38.238 --> 05:40.072
No, no...
No, it's fine.

05:40.174 --> 05:44.076
I'm aware of the trouble
Robert has been causing you.

05:44.178 --> 05:48.647
Well, maybe I could do
something about that.

05:48.749 --> 05:52.551
You deliver the union vote
in Illinois for John,

05:52.653 --> 05:55.053
and I will make
sure that Robert

05:55.155 --> 05:57.589
doesn't pose any
more problems for you.

06:05.866 --> 06:07.833
We'll think about it.

06:07.935 --> 06:09.201
Fair enough.

06:11.605 --> 06:15.507
Joe Kennedy had connections to
the Outfit that ran very deep,

06:15.609 --> 06:19.177
and as far back as the 1920s,
he was meeting

06:19.279 --> 06:22.581
and doing business with
prominent bootleggers.

06:22.683 --> 06:25.484
And so Kennedy is reigniting
his relationship

06:25.586 --> 06:28.019
with underworld
figures in Chicago

06:28.122 --> 06:30.522
in anticipation of the election.

06:30.624 --> 06:34.659
♪♪

06:36.630 --> 06:39.131
President in our favor.

06:39.233 --> 06:41.833
Could solve a lot of problems.

06:41.935 --> 06:43.802
Yeah.

06:43.904 --> 06:45.704
And Robert Kennedy
gone for good.

06:47.408 --> 06:48.907
Why not?

06:51.245 --> 06:53.178
Sam Giancana's latest assignment

06:53.280 --> 06:55.981
could get him back in good
standing with Accardo.

06:58.318 --> 07:00.719
All he has to do is help
John F. Kennedy

07:00.821 --> 07:02.354
get elected president.

07:06.794 --> 07:08.827
I remember, guys were sent to
all of us guys,

07:08.929 --> 07:10.896
and they said, "We had to get
Kennedy in office."

07:10.998 --> 07:14.666
And I said "Who wants to vote
for that guy?" You know.

07:14.768 --> 07:16.735
Sam wants it done.

07:16.837 --> 07:20.672
"If we get this Irishman in
office, we got it made."

07:26.013 --> 07:30.081
Kennedy's campaign captures
the imagination of the country.

07:30.184 --> 07:31.883
But as election day nears,

07:31.985 --> 07:36.021
his fight against Richard Nixon
for the White House tightens,

07:36.123 --> 07:38.590
turning the Outfit's
home state of Illinois

07:38.692 --> 07:41.259
into a key battleground.

07:41.361 --> 07:44.362
In that 1960 election,
Illinois was a critical state.

07:44.465 --> 07:46.498
And look how close these
elections are,

07:46.600 --> 07:49.000
and they're decided by a county
here and a county there.

07:49.102 --> 07:52.103
It throws
the entire election off.

07:52.206 --> 07:53.572
<i>A record number of Americans,</i>

07:53.674 --> 07:56.541
<i> upwards of 67 million
go to the polls</i>

07:56.643 --> 07:59.911
<i> to elect the 35th President of
the United States.</i>

08:00.013 --> 08:03.515
<i> Citizens from Maine to Hawaii
record their choices...</i>

08:03.617 --> 08:04.783
Okay here?

08:04.885 --> 08:06.084
Okay.

08:07.120 --> 08:08.386
Good, three more times.

08:08.489 --> 08:10.856
Same guy.
Change.

08:10.958 --> 08:13.225
So where do we stand?

08:13.327 --> 08:15.727
The votes, uh,
are still coming in, okay?

08:15.829 --> 08:17.929
Those union votes
will come, I promise you.

08:18.031 --> 08:19.664
You'll see a peak, you will.

08:21.502 --> 08:23.168
You better not mess this up.

08:26.139 --> 08:27.772
I know.

08:30.344 --> 08:34.011
♪♪

08:35.549 --> 08:38.616
With the race so close,

08:38.719 --> 08:41.852
the winner isn't declared
until the next day.

08:48.028 --> 08:52.898
<i>While there are still some
results still to come in,</i>

08:53.000 --> 08:55.500
<i> uh, if the present
trend continues,</i>

08:55.602 --> 08:58.003
<i> uh, Mr. Kennedy,
Senator Kennedy</i>

08:58.105 --> 09:01.072
<i> will be the next
President of the United States.</i>

09:08.749 --> 09:10.382
We just got a president.

09:16.890 --> 09:18.189
We did it.

09:19.359 --> 09:20.559
Yeah.

09:22.062 --> 09:23.328
Unbelievable.

09:27.134 --> 09:28.733
To us.

09:30.270 --> 09:31.169
To us.

09:32.539 --> 09:34.539
And the Presidency.

09:34.641 --> 09:36.341
And our President.

09:44.284 --> 09:48.119
Good job.

09:48.221 --> 09:51.690
Did you just say
something nice to me?

09:51.758 --> 09:52.924
Shut up.

09:54.962 --> 09:56.528
If you look at the numbers of
that election,

09:56.630 --> 09:58.296
you could say that
the Outfit delivering

09:58.398 --> 10:01.700
those votes in Chicago
were instrumental

10:01.802 --> 10:04.836
in getting Jack Kennedy
elected President.

10:04.905 --> 10:09.207
For Giancana,
JFK's election is a huge triumph

10:09.309 --> 10:11.209
that proves
the disgraced gangster

10:11.311 --> 10:14.346
still has something to offer,

10:14.448 --> 10:17.182
and he wastes
no time celebrating.

10:18.352 --> 10:22.754
Everybody drink,
come on!

10:22.856 --> 10:25.090
That is good.

10:25.192 --> 10:28.226
Sam Giancana is kind of
a funny gangster, um...

10:28.328 --> 10:32.063
He would boast about stealing
the election for Kennedy.

10:34.635 --> 10:37.702
Whoo! To me and us
and mainly the ladies.

10:41.108 --> 10:45.276
♪♪

10:45.379 --> 10:49.514
But just weeks after
John F. Kennedy takes office,

10:49.616 --> 10:52.817
his brother, Robert is named
Attorney General.

10:55.989 --> 10:58.690
The face of organized
crime has changed.

10:58.792 --> 11:00.925
Though crimes
of violence still occur,

11:01.028 --> 11:03.695
the modern criminal has become
more sophisticated

11:03.797 --> 11:07.132
about the planning and
perpetration of his activities.

11:07.234 --> 11:10.535
<i>And we are working very hard to
develop a coordinated effort</i>

11:10.637 --> 11:13.371
<i> to curb the hoodlums
and racketeers</i>

11:13.473 --> 11:15.173
<i> and put them in jail.</i>

11:18.845 --> 11:20.478
The mob is outraged.

11:22.649 --> 11:25.984
They were angry
about the fact that--

11:26.086 --> 11:28.386
"How could this be happening
after what we did

11:28.488 --> 11:32.390
for the father,
for Joe Kennedy?"

11:32.492 --> 11:36.294
After months of failing
to put a stop to Giancana,

11:36.396 --> 11:38.963
Robert F. Kennedy now
has the power he needs

11:39.066 --> 11:42.767
to launch a full scale
investigation into the mobster.

11:46.572 --> 11:50.175
♪♪

11:53.814 --> 11:56.214
To the Chicago Mob's surprise,

11:56.316 --> 11:58.450
when Robert F. Kennedy
takes office

11:58.552 --> 12:02.787
as the new U.S. Attorney General
in 1961,

12:02.889 --> 12:06.191
he makes his top priority
going after organized crime.

12:07.861 --> 12:10.795
And one of his primary targets
is the Outfit.

12:12.699 --> 12:13.598
Where do we stand
on Vegas?

12:13.700 --> 12:15.166
Still nothing.

12:15.268 --> 12:19.471
Nevada's Attorney General
has been unresponsive.

12:19.573 --> 12:20.839
Then get him
on the phone,

12:20.941 --> 12:22.941
and tell him if Nevada
won't cooperate,

12:23.043 --> 12:25.677
I will raid every
one of their casinos.

12:25.779 --> 12:28.747
I will shut down gambling across
the entire state if I have to.

12:28.849 --> 12:30.515
Yes, sir.

12:30.617 --> 12:32.183
And then in Chicago?

12:32.285 --> 12:34.352
How many agents
do I have on the ground?

12:34.454 --> 12:35.754
Ten.

12:35.856 --> 12:37.255
Ten?

12:37.357 --> 12:40.525
No, I need 60 agents
down there immediately.

12:40.627 --> 12:42.460
I want to know what
Giancana and Accardo

12:42.562 --> 12:44.696
are up to every
second of the day.

12:44.798 --> 12:47.766
If those two buy a stick of gum,
I wanna know about it.

12:47.868 --> 12:49.334
Absolutely, sir.

12:49.436 --> 12:50.668
Good.

12:52.305 --> 12:55.140
It's an interesting question
about why Robert Kennedy

12:55.242 --> 12:58.309
was so determined
to go after the Mafia.

12:58.411 --> 13:02.013
Robert Kennedy did see the world
in black and white terms,

13:02.115 --> 13:03.815
much more than his brother.

13:03.917 --> 13:09.687
He sees going after organized
crime as a justified mission

13:09.790 --> 13:12.557
and as a way
of building his own fame

13:12.659 --> 13:15.960
and, and his launching
his own political career.

13:16.062 --> 13:17.562
Good?
Yes, sir.

13:17.664 --> 13:19.364
Yes, sir.
Gentlemen.

13:19.466 --> 13:24.702
♪♪

13:29.676 --> 13:33.077
As Kennedy's investigation
ramps up,

13:33.180 --> 13:36.915
he goes out of his way to target
mob boss Sam Giancana.

13:39.686 --> 13:40.852
<i>Hello?</i>

13:40.954 --> 13:44.088
Hey, sweetheart,
how are you?

13:44.191 --> 13:45.890
<i>Missing you.</i>

13:47.494 --> 13:49.160
<i>You visiting soon?
Yeah,</i>

13:49.262 --> 13:50.862
<i> I've been meaning
to come out there as, uh,</i>

13:50.964 --> 13:52.197
<i> soon as possible.</i>

13:55.802 --> 13:57.202
<i> How about Saturday?</i>

13:58.338 --> 14:00.738
<i>In time for dinner?</i>

14:00.841 --> 14:02.874
Yeah, I'll take you
to your favorite spot.

14:07.681 --> 14:10.048
Kennedy was willing
to go after the mob

14:10.150 --> 14:13.885
by any means necessary.

14:13.987 --> 14:16.921
A lot of it was done through
surveillance and wiretaps

14:17.023 --> 14:18.923
that were unauthorized by law.

14:21.228 --> 14:23.361
Over the coming months,

14:23.463 --> 14:25.697
Giancana is followed
everywhere he goes.

14:25.799 --> 14:29.467
♪♪

14:34.007 --> 14:38.843
Sam Giancana is being trailed
by federal agents 24/7.

14:40.680 --> 14:43.047
They stake out his house.

14:43.149 --> 14:46.951
They're literally following
him on the golf course.

14:47.053 --> 14:49.821
This was without
question harassment.

15:08.341 --> 15:09.707
Why aren't you eating?

15:22.289 --> 15:25.323
The FBI clearly knew that
Giancana was fairly unstable.

15:25.425 --> 15:27.959
He was prone
to violent outbursts,

15:28.061 --> 15:29.494
getting very, very upset.

15:29.562 --> 15:33.164
So, their strategy
is to try and get to him

15:33.266 --> 15:35.633
by needling him
in various ways.

15:39.940 --> 15:42.674
They're just trying
to get a rise out of you.

15:42.776 --> 15:44.976
Don't give them
the satisfaction.

15:50.116 --> 15:52.050
Sam...

15:54.621 --> 15:55.853
Something the matter?

15:55.956 --> 15:57.488
I catch you two snooping
around me again,

15:57.590 --> 16:00.024
and I promise you
it'll be the last time.

16:00.126 --> 16:02.961
Are you threatening
a federal agent?

16:03.063 --> 16:06.731
♪♪

16:15.175 --> 16:16.674
We're going.

16:18.478 --> 16:21.245
♪♪

16:25.118 --> 16:28.686
♪♪

16:30.323 --> 16:33.424
Sir, I think you
want to see this.

16:39.499 --> 16:40.898
Is this a joke?

16:41.001 --> 16:42.266
No, sir.

16:44.471 --> 16:46.938
With the FBI tailing
his every move,

16:47.040 --> 16:50.875
Sam Giancana decides to hit back

16:50.944 --> 16:54.479
and sues the federal government
for harassment.

17:00.252 --> 17:04.255
♪♪

17:04.357 --> 17:07.290
After being wiretapped
by Robert F. Kennedy

17:07.394 --> 17:10.494
and tailed around the clock
by the FBI,

17:10.597 --> 17:15.333
acting mob boss Sam Giancana
makes an unprecedented move

17:15.435 --> 17:18.770
and files a lawsuit against
the federal government.

17:20.205 --> 17:22.306
Mr. Giancana?

17:22.409 --> 17:24.242
The court finds in your favor.

17:26.880 --> 17:29.614
Court is adjourned.

17:29.716 --> 17:33.751
In the summer of 1963,
a judge rules that the FBI

17:33.853 --> 17:35.920
has gone too far,

17:36.022 --> 17:40.691
ordering them to limit their
surveillance on Giancana.

17:40.794 --> 17:42.860
As a private citizen,
he's being harassed

17:42.929 --> 17:45.129
by these federal agents,
so, you know,

17:45.231 --> 17:46.497
"Let me take 'em to court."

17:46.599 --> 17:47.832
He's got nothing to lose.

17:47.934 --> 17:49.734
He kicks in this lawsuit
and he wins.

17:54.541 --> 17:58.876
♪♪

17:58.978 --> 18:00.378
Prick.

18:02.148 --> 18:04.849
But Giancana's victory
is short-lived.

18:07.620 --> 18:10.688
By suing the government,
Giancana really put

18:10.790 --> 18:14.058
a target on his back
in a way that

18:14.160 --> 18:17.528
was very reminiscent of Capone,

18:17.630 --> 18:20.431
I'm sure, for Accardo.

18:31.077 --> 18:34.745
Fed up with Giancana's antics,
Tony Accardo calls a meeting

18:34.848 --> 18:38.683
with his co-boss, Paul Ricca,
who's recently been released

18:38.785 --> 18:41.018
after serving
27 months in prison.

18:42.322 --> 18:44.689
First, he kidnaps Eddie Jones.

18:44.791 --> 18:46.724
I let it slide.

18:47.694 --> 18:49.794
Then he goes to the Tribune.

18:50.830 --> 18:52.997
I turn a blind eye.

18:53.099 --> 18:55.399
Now he sues the FBI.

18:55.502 --> 18:57.268
I'm done.

18:58.638 --> 19:00.371
If he carries on this way,

19:00.473 --> 19:02.740
he's gonna get us
all busted.

19:02.842 --> 19:04.609
What do you suppose we do?

19:04.711 --> 19:07.345
We settle things...

19:07.447 --> 19:08.646
permanently.

19:13.453 --> 19:14.619
All right.

19:17.557 --> 19:19.223
I won't get in the way.

19:21.494 --> 19:23.528
Well, in organized crime,
you don't want to kill anybody

19:23.630 --> 19:26.697
you don't have to, but...

19:26.799 --> 19:28.866
the Giancana lawsuit
against the FBI

19:28.968 --> 19:31.402
is probably another straw
on the camel's back.

19:33.373 --> 19:35.806
Paul Ricca finally has enough.

19:39.312 --> 19:43.414
♪♪

19:47.487 --> 19:50.221
<i>With the gate closed,
7-1/2 with the gate open.</i>

19:50.323 --> 19:51.722
<i> Plush floors
and big wide doors</i>

19:51.824 --> 19:54.058
<i> give you this kind
of easy entrance.</i>

19:54.160 --> 19:55.326
<i> So simple to clean too.</i>

19:55.428 --> 19:57.662
<i> Just whisk out dust and dirt.</i>

19:57.764 --> 20:00.131
<i> From stem to stern, plenty of
head room, leg room</i>

20:00.233 --> 20:03.801
<i> and seat width for,
that's right, six passengers.</i>

20:03.903 --> 20:06.170
<i> And you can ride in comfort
in any kind of weather</i>

20:06.272 --> 20:07.972
<i> with the top gate open.</i>

20:08.074 --> 20:10.808
<i> Complete ventilation
even when it rains.</i>

20:10.910 --> 20:14.478
<i> Do yourself a favor,
see your...</i>

20:20.119 --> 20:21.786
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

20:21.888 --> 20:24.989
<i> we have a bit of information.</i>

20:25.091 --> 20:27.758
<i> President Kennedy and
Texas Governor John Connelly</i>

20:27.860 --> 20:32.830
<i> shot by an assassin
today in Dallas, Texas.</i>

20:32.932 --> 20:36.467
<i> We do not know officially at
this moment</i>

20:36.569 --> 20:40.805
<i> as to whether the President
is alive or dead.</i>

20:46.546 --> 20:49.880
Before Ricca and Accardo can put
their plan in motion,

20:49.983 --> 20:52.483
an event changes
the course of history.

20:53.553 --> 20:58.055
♪♪

21:00.960 --> 21:05.630
On November 22, 1963,

21:05.732 --> 21:08.032
President John F. Kennedy,

21:08.134 --> 21:11.369
the man the Outfit helped elect,

21:11.471 --> 21:15.539
is shot and killed in Dallas
at the age of 46.

21:18.278 --> 21:21.946
♪♪

21:33.493 --> 21:37.194
♪♪

21:40.300 --> 21:43.567
After his brother
is assassinated,

21:43.670 --> 21:45.169
Robert F. Kennedy steps down

21:45.271 --> 21:49.040
from his post
as Attorney General.

21:49.142 --> 21:53.010
I would say no group benefited
more from the assassination

21:53.112 --> 21:57.615
of John F. Kennedy
than the Outfit.

21:57.717 --> 22:00.851
Bobby Kennedy
as Attorney General had put

22:00.953 --> 22:04.722
tremendous resources
into investigating

22:04.824 --> 22:07.591
and indicting
organized crime figures.

22:07.694 --> 22:12.029
And those investigations dropped
to almost nothing

22:12.131 --> 22:14.265
after, uh, the assassination.

22:23.576 --> 22:25.576
<i>This he describes as the
government of organized</i>

22:25.678 --> 22:27.778
<i>gambling, narcotics peddling...</i>

22:27.880 --> 22:31.315
But a new threat
to the Outfit soon emerges

22:31.417 --> 22:33.284
when the government
begins an investigation

22:33.386 --> 22:37.988
into Kennedy's assassination,
with rumors already circulating

22:38.091 --> 22:40.991
that the mafia
could have been involved.

22:41.094 --> 22:43.828
There are a lot of people who
think organized crime

22:43.930 --> 22:45.162
had something to do with it.

22:45.264 --> 22:47.932
Was Lee Harvey Oswald
a mob hit man?

22:48.034 --> 22:51.068
And here's
Jack Ruby just coming in

22:51.170 --> 22:55.573
and shooting Lee Harvey Oswald
on live television.

22:55.675 --> 22:57.441
How could this happen?

22:57.543 --> 23:00.378
Nobody knows, and I don't know
that we ever will.

23:04.283 --> 23:06.951
With pressure on the mob
intensifying,

23:07.053 --> 23:10.955
Accardo knows it's no time
for a high profile hit,

23:11.057 --> 23:13.190
so he has to come up
with another way

23:13.292 --> 23:17.695
to get rid of his
second-in-command for good.

23:22.434 --> 23:25.603
♪♪

23:43.656 --> 23:45.823
You wanted to see me?

23:47.960 --> 23:50.828
Sit down.

24:02.742 --> 24:05.142
Take those
stupid glasses off.

24:13.152 --> 24:15.519
Take them off.

24:24.197 --> 24:26.297
Happy?

24:28.868 --> 24:33.838
I'm going to lay out what's
going to happen very clearly.

24:33.940 --> 24:35.306
And I don't want to hear a word
out of your mouth

24:35.408 --> 24:36.607
until I'm finished.

24:36.742 --> 24:38.776
At which point,

24:38.878 --> 24:41.445
the only words I want to hear
from you

24:41.547 --> 24:46.517
are, "Yes, I understand."

24:50.790 --> 24:52.590
What the hell is this?

24:52.692 --> 24:54.859
What did I just say?

25:02.635 --> 25:04.635
After today,
you're gonna have

25:04.737 --> 25:07.104
nothing more
to do with the organization.

25:07.206 --> 25:10.174
Immediately after
you leave here,

25:10.276 --> 25:13.143
you're going to pack your bags
for Mexico,

25:13.246 --> 25:17.681
and you're never coming back.

25:23.422 --> 25:25.756
You're really letting
him do this?

25:28.461 --> 25:31.729
This is coming
from both of us.

25:31.797 --> 25:34.865
Hey...

25:34.967 --> 25:37.568
Hey.

25:37.670 --> 25:41.605
You should be thankful you get
to leave with your life.

25:43.442 --> 25:47.678
It's the best deal you're
ever going to get from me.

25:47.780 --> 25:52.182
The power of Accardo
at that stage was so absolute,

25:52.285 --> 25:54.418
he really didn't have to kill
Giancana.

25:54.520 --> 25:57.621
He could truly just push him
aside,

25:57.690 --> 26:00.624
as far aside as Mexico.

26:22.014 --> 26:24.715
Tony Accardo and Paul Ricca

26:24.817 --> 26:29.386
force Sam Giancana
out of the organization.

26:29.488 --> 26:32.423
But even with Giancana gone,

26:32.525 --> 26:35.893
Accardo knows the Feds won't
stop coming after them.

26:35.995 --> 26:40.998
♪♪

26:46.505 --> 26:48.739
If Tony Accardo
has learned anything

26:48.841 --> 26:51.408
from his mentor Al Capone,

26:51.510 --> 26:56.280
it's that a high profile
in the Mafia never pays off.

26:59.752 --> 27:04.254
And now, Accardo's determined
to tie up loose ends

27:04.357 --> 27:08.025
before the government has
a chance to take him down.

27:10.696 --> 27:13.163
Tony Accardo was very, very good
at his chosen profession.

27:13.265 --> 27:17.968
He was very, very good at
avoiding getting imprisoned.

27:18.070 --> 27:21.305
Accardo was also good at
insulating himself from things,

27:21.407 --> 27:22.740
and therefore made it harder

27:22.842 --> 27:25.042
for the federal government
to get at him.

27:38.457 --> 27:40.157
Gentlemen,
good to see you.

27:40.259 --> 27:41.458
Good to see you.

27:41.527 --> 27:44.528
Good to see you.
Take a seat, please.

27:44.630 --> 27:51.201
On March 27, 1967, Accardo sells
one of his top Vegas hotels,

27:51.303 --> 27:53.037
the Desert Inn,

27:53.139 --> 27:56.707
to eccentric billionaire,
Howard Hughes.

27:58.444 --> 28:00.911
Now, when Howard Hughes
buys the DI,

28:00.980 --> 28:05.049
he's cashing out
organized crime interests.

28:05.151 --> 28:07.851
They don't have the
organizational responsibility.

28:07.953 --> 28:09.653
Now it's Hughes' problem.

28:09.755 --> 28:16.694
And they get a big influx of
cash because Hughes had money.

28:18.130 --> 28:20.064
Accardo's deal with Hughes

28:20.166 --> 28:22.499
ushers in a new era
in Las Vegas.

28:22.601 --> 28:24.902
Hughes ends up cashing out
the Outfit

28:25.004 --> 28:26.737
and other investors
at the Sands.

28:26.839 --> 28:29.206
He ends up buying
the Frontier Hotel,

28:29.308 --> 28:32.242
which always had connections
to the Outfit in Chicago.

28:32.344 --> 28:34.178
♪♪

28:34.280 --> 28:39.316
Then, in 1969,
the Nevada Gaming Commission

28:39.418 --> 28:44.221
makes it legal for corporations
to buy casinos.

28:44.323 --> 28:46.657
The Corporate Gaming Act
is Nevada's effort

28:46.759 --> 28:50.360
to attract Wall Street capital.

28:50.463 --> 28:53.430
This is their chance to
legitimize the industry.

28:53.532 --> 28:57.935
The Outfit cashes out
more of their casinos,

28:58.037 --> 28:59.770
and according to some,

28:59.872 --> 29:04.341
they walk away with an estimated
$400 million in today's money.

29:04.443 --> 29:06.543
♪♪

29:06.645 --> 29:09.680
When the Chicago Outfit exited
Las Vegas at the time,

29:09.782 --> 29:13.117
they knew their time
was coming to an end.

29:13.219 --> 29:14.518
They sold out for a good profit.

29:14.620 --> 29:16.954
They had their day,
and they moved on.

29:17.056 --> 29:20.090
♪♪

29:27.066 --> 29:30.968
But shortly after the Outfit
cashes out of Vegas,

29:31.070 --> 29:34.972
Tony Accardo receives
devastating news.

29:35.074 --> 29:37.307
♪♪

29:37.409 --> 29:42.579
On October 11, 1972,
his friend of 40 years

29:42.681 --> 29:45.415
who served with him
under Al Capone

29:45.518 --> 29:47.584
and helped create
one of the most powerful

29:47.686 --> 29:50.120
crime organizations
in the country,

29:50.222 --> 29:53.991
Paul Ricca,
dies of a heart attack.

29:54.093 --> 29:58.428
♪♪

29:58.531 --> 30:01.298
Paul Ricca,
his legacy was ushering in

30:01.400 --> 30:03.600
the reign of Tony Accardo.

30:03.702 --> 30:10.507
He was someone who emulated
a lot of corporate America.

30:10.609 --> 30:14.912
This was something he initiated
which Accardo picked up.

30:15.014 --> 30:20.450
They were really looking at
major businesses

30:20.553 --> 30:22.953
and how they were organized
to determine

30:23.055 --> 30:26.323
how they would organize the mob
here in Chicago.

30:26.425 --> 30:29.793
♪♪

30:36.635 --> 30:40.370
Paul "The Waiter" Ricca,
the boss of organized crime

30:40.472 --> 30:43.273
in Chicago
and in the United States,

30:43.375 --> 30:45.676
and the reason people
don't hear about him

30:45.778 --> 30:48.011
is because he was
a master criminal.

30:48.113 --> 30:51.715
And master criminals don't
want to be heard about.

31:00.893 --> 31:03.994
Not long after
Paul Ricca's death,

31:04.096 --> 31:07.064
Tony Accardo gets more bad news.

31:07.166 --> 31:09.566
You're not
going to like this.

31:09.668 --> 31:11.401
What is it?

31:11.503 --> 31:14.071
It's Giancana.

31:14.173 --> 31:16.373
He's back in town.

31:16.475 --> 31:20.544
Word is, he's been
talking with the Feds.

31:23.182 --> 31:25.916
Thanks for
letting me know.

31:26.018 --> 31:29.019
♪♪

31:33.125 --> 31:36.593
That prick.

31:36.695 --> 31:40.731
With nearly three decades worth
of information on the Outfit,

31:40.833 --> 31:45.102
Accardo knows that Giancana
is not only a threat to him

31:45.204 --> 31:49.539
but to the future
of the entire Chicago Mafia.

31:49.642 --> 31:52.643
♪♪

31:56.481 --> 32:00.984
♪♪

32:01.086 --> 32:04.821
After seven years of forced
exile in Mexico,

32:04.924 --> 32:07.658
Sam Giancana,
the number one threat

32:07.760 --> 32:12.729
to Outfit boss Tony Accardo
is back in town.

32:12.831 --> 32:14.865
♪♪

32:17.870 --> 32:21.271
And word quickly gets out

32:21.373 --> 32:23.440
that he's talking
to the Feds.

32:23.542 --> 32:26.009
♪♪

32:26.111 --> 32:28.245
If Sam Giancana had walked
into the FBI office

32:28.347 --> 32:29.646
and offered his services,

32:29.748 --> 32:31.281
it would have been
a golden opportunity.

32:31.383 --> 32:32.749
He would have been a
high enough ranking official.

32:32.851 --> 32:36.153
It would have been
unheard of cooperation.

32:36.255 --> 32:40.624
♪♪

32:45.564 --> 32:49.967
♪♪

33:12.491 --> 33:14.891
Sam!

33:14.994 --> 33:16.927
In here.

33:19.832 --> 33:23.367
I'm cooking sausage,
you want some?

33:23.435 --> 33:25.369
Yeah.

33:30.943 --> 33:32.476
How was Mexico?

33:32.578 --> 33:34.911
Mexico...

33:35.014 --> 33:36.213
You'd love it
down there.

33:36.315 --> 33:37.247
Yeah?

33:37.349 --> 33:38.782
Yeah.

33:42.855 --> 33:44.921
Yeah, but it's good
to be back.

33:45.024 --> 33:47.691
I'm gonna make some
new moves out here.

33:47.793 --> 33:50.694
Joe know about it?

33:50.796 --> 33:53.330
He won't like it.

33:53.432 --> 33:58.268
But he never liked
anything I did anyway.

33:58.337 --> 34:01.938
The one thing
I've learned, though--

34:02.041 --> 34:03.240
No one's gonna
look out for you

34:03.342 --> 34:06.276
except for you,
you know?

34:19.358 --> 34:25.795
On June 19, 1975,
Sam Giancana is shot to death

34:25.898 --> 34:30.067
in the basement of his suburban
home in Oak Park, Illinois,

34:30.168 --> 34:32.469
by an unknown assassin.

34:32.571 --> 34:36.440
♪♪

34:36.507 --> 34:38.909
One speculation is,
whoever came,

34:39.011 --> 34:40.877
he knew personally,

34:40.978 --> 34:42.612
which would be natural,
you know,

34:42.714 --> 34:45.114
because he was at risk
at that point.

34:45.217 --> 34:47.451
He would not have
let anybody in that house

34:47.553 --> 34:49.820
who didn't befriend him.

34:49.922 --> 34:53.322
♪♪

34:53.425 --> 34:55.158
Giancana's strengths
as a gangster

34:55.260 --> 34:58.562
was his ability to make money,

34:58.664 --> 35:01.498
his ability to use violence.

35:04.903 --> 35:10.006
His weaknesses were that,
the publicity that he garnered,

35:10.109 --> 35:12.943
he became just,
just too hot to handle.

35:13.045 --> 35:14.811
Again, again!

35:14.913 --> 35:18.381
He had to be removed
'cause he just knew too much.

35:18.450 --> 35:20.350
♪♪

35:20.452 --> 35:25.622
To this day, speculation
surrounds Giancana's death.

35:25.724 --> 35:28.525
♪♪

35:28.627 --> 35:32.028
But for some,
there's little doubt.

35:32.131 --> 35:33.763
♪♪

35:33.866 --> 35:36.766
Absolutely, Tony Accardo ordered
the ultimate murder

35:36.869 --> 35:38.335
of Sam Giancana.

35:38.437 --> 35:41.338
You do not whack anybody
out in that group

35:41.440 --> 35:44.474
without getting permission,
plain and simple.

35:44.576 --> 35:48.778
♪♪

35:48.881 --> 35:51.882
<i>Private funeral services for
Sam Giancana were held today</i>

35:51.984 --> 35:54.151
<i> and John Drummond was there.</i>

35:54.253 --> 35:56.887
Despite Giancana's status
in the Outfit...

35:56.989 --> 35:58.655
<i>...were on hand to pay
their last respects,</i>

35:58.724 --> 36:01.558
<i>Outfit bigwigs were conspicuous
by their absence</i>

36:01.660 --> 36:03.493
<i> at the services held at the...</i>

36:03.595 --> 36:05.795
...Tony Accardo orders
that no member

36:05.898 --> 36:08.999
of the Chicago Outfit
attend his funeral.

36:09.101 --> 36:12.602
♪♪

36:17.176 --> 36:21.044
Then, just over a month
after Giancana's death,

36:21.146 --> 36:27.083
outspoken former Outfit partner,
Jimmy Hoffa, disappears

36:27.186 --> 36:29.920
the same day he agreed to meet
with two men

36:30.022 --> 36:31.922
connected to the mob.

36:32.024 --> 36:38.695
♪♪

36:38.797 --> 36:42.032
When Jimmy Hoffa was killed,
my mother said,

36:42.134 --> 36:44.067
"They threw him
in the Detroit River,

36:44.169 --> 36:47.237
and nobody can survive that."

36:47.339 --> 36:49.272
Well, who killed Hoffa?

36:49.374 --> 36:52.909
It's pretty clear there are
organized crime connections.

36:53.011 --> 36:58.114
And whoever did it, the Chicago
Outfit had to be okay with it.

36:58.217 --> 37:02.619
♪♪

37:02.721 --> 37:06.022
Jimmy Hoffa's remains
are never found,

37:06.124 --> 37:08.225
but many believe
his disappearance

37:08.327 --> 37:12.362
is all part of Accardo's plan to
tie up loose ends in the Mafia

37:12.464 --> 37:17.834
so that he can finally leave
his life as a mob boss behind.

37:21.105 --> 37:24.608
♪♪

37:26.945 --> 37:29.980
In the wake of Al Capone's
enormous success

37:30.082 --> 37:32.315
and spectacular downfall,

37:32.417 --> 37:35.986
only one Outfit member
from his era remains--

37:36.088 --> 37:39.856
his former bodyguard,
Tony Accardo.

37:39.958 --> 37:42.859
♪♪

37:42.961 --> 37:46.830
Tony Accardo's legacy
as a gangster,

37:46.932 --> 37:51.468
I would have to say was probably
one of the smoothest...

37:51.570 --> 37:54.137
I almost want to use
the word "unassuming,"

37:54.206 --> 37:56.706
but if you knew Accardo,
he knew what he was doing.

37:56.808 --> 38:00.043
♪♪

38:00.145 --> 38:04.114
To maintain a low profile,
Accardo kept a job

38:04.216 --> 38:08.118
as a beer salesman
for Fox Head Brewing Company,

38:08.220 --> 38:11.321
even filing
income tax returns.

38:11.423 --> 38:13.523
But over the years,
he also built

38:13.625 --> 38:16.059
a diverse business portfolio

38:16.161 --> 38:18.895
that included trucking
companies, restaurants,

38:18.997 --> 38:23.733
coal and lumber operations,
earning him an untold fortune.

38:26.772 --> 38:31.708
♪♪

38:34.846 --> 38:37.514
I mean, you look at this
individual who had

38:37.616 --> 38:41.985
a sixth grade education,
and he becomes,

38:42.087 --> 38:46.423
over the course of his
50-year reign of the mob,

38:46.525 --> 38:48.825
an extremely
sophisticated person

38:48.927 --> 38:52.562
who really took organized crime
to a level

38:52.664 --> 38:56.366
that no other
mob leader took it.

38:56.468 --> 38:58.368
♪♪

38:58.470 --> 39:02.105
Tony Accardo
should be known to people

39:02.207 --> 39:06.376
as a true legend
in organized crime.

39:06.478 --> 39:07.777
♪♪

39:07.879 --> 39:09.079
And he isn't.

39:09.181 --> 39:11.381
And I think
he wanted it that way.

39:11.483 --> 39:16.419
♪♪

39:20.992 --> 39:24.561
In 1992, after a career
in the mafia

39:24.663 --> 39:27.964
spanning nearly 70 years,

39:28.066 --> 39:32.235
the mob boss dies peacefully,
surrounded by family...

39:32.337 --> 39:34.971
♪♪

39:35.073 --> 39:38.808
having never spent
a day in prison.

39:38.910 --> 39:41.845
♪♪

39:44.416 --> 39:45.715
♪♪

39:45.817 --> 39:47.917
But while Accardo
earns a reputation

39:48.019 --> 39:51.321
as one of the most powerful
mafia kingpins ever,

39:51.423 --> 39:53.623
The Outfit's success goes back

39:53.725 --> 39:55.592
to the early days of
bootlegging,

39:55.694 --> 39:58.628
when Al Capone's mentor,
Johnny Torrio,

39:58.730 --> 40:02.499
decided to structure the Chicago
mob to run like a business.

40:02.601 --> 40:04.501
We'll be producing
enough booze to supply

40:04.603 --> 40:08.004
every one of your joints
for pennies on the dollar.

40:08.106 --> 40:11.875
Johnny Torrio, more than anybody
else, invented the concept

40:11.943 --> 40:14.511
of organized crime
and of syndicates

40:14.613 --> 40:16.780
and of lines of authority.

40:16.848 --> 40:19.115
♪♪

40:19.217 --> 40:23.353
Al Capone continued
Torrio's methods,

40:23.455 --> 40:27.857
but also expanded the Italian
gang's grip on the city

40:27.959 --> 40:30.193
by ruthlessly
taking over territory.

40:30.295 --> 40:32.529
We need to hit them,
hit them hard.

40:37.436 --> 40:39.536
His hold on Chicago rackets,

40:39.638 --> 40:43.006
and eventually rackets beyond,
was extraordinary.

40:43.108 --> 40:45.175
This is what happens.

40:45.277 --> 40:47.043
No, please--

40:47.145 --> 40:49.479
♪♪

40:49.581 --> 40:51.981
Maybe of all the gangsters
that ever lived,

40:52.083 --> 40:53.883
Al Capone is the most famous.

40:53.985 --> 40:57.220
What made him stand out
was a certain charisma,

40:57.322 --> 40:59.522
was a style that Al had.

40:59.624 --> 41:02.358
He wasn't afraid to express
himself vocally...

41:02.461 --> 41:04.360
There's enough business
here for all of us

41:04.463 --> 41:06.663
without killing each other
in the streets like animals.

41:06.765 --> 41:09.165
...and to be an outgoing guy.

41:09.267 --> 41:11.367
That, combined with
the historical record

41:11.470 --> 41:14.003
of what he did,
in terms of his violence

41:14.105 --> 41:15.872
and the way that he lived,

41:15.974 --> 41:19.375
it just makes him memorable
for all eternity.

41:19.444 --> 41:21.377
♪♪

41:21.480 --> 41:24.314
In the wake of Capone's success,

41:24.416 --> 41:27.650
Frank Nitti, Paul Ricca,
and Tony Accardo

41:27.752 --> 41:30.553
took what they learned
from the kingpin

41:30.655 --> 41:32.388
and expanded the Outfit

41:32.491 --> 41:35.658
to become the largest organized
crime group in America.

41:35.760 --> 41:38.394
This is a beautiful
ledger sheet.

41:38.497 --> 41:39.696
♪♪

41:39.798 --> 41:41.397
In the process,

41:41.500 --> 41:44.100
Al Capone
and the Chicago Outfit

41:44.202 --> 41:46.369
changed the course
of American history.

41:46.471 --> 41:49.539
We just got
a President.

41:49.641 --> 41:55.078
New York gets the publicity,
New York is the soap opera.

41:55.180 --> 41:59.315
But for most of
the 20th century,

41:59.384 --> 42:04.053
Chicago and the leaders,
who you don't even know,

42:04.155 --> 42:08.057
were the ones who ran things
from one end to the other--

42:08.159 --> 42:12.629
the gambling industry,
the movie industry.

42:12.731 --> 42:15.098
Always a pleasure.

42:15.200 --> 42:18.301
That was the genius
of the Outfit.

42:18.403 --> 42:23.403
-SubRip & non-HI by Rapunzel-
